    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "\r\n\r\n> Thanks, so just 2 components, DTL and the L2geth.\r\n> \r\n> Does the L2Geth gossip with other L2geth nodes on the network via P2P to get pending transactions? I know that the sequencer has no mempool and just directly append the TX in FIFO order to the state transitions, but would L2Geth broadcast pending TX into the network and the Sequencer?\r\n\r\nCurrently, no, there is no L2 p2p network. This will change as part of the upcoming Bedrock upgrade where p2p will be reintroduced. At the moment, the DTL (when running in L1 sync mode) will get blocks directly from L1 (Ethereum). This will always lag a bit behind the L2 system because the Sequencer can wait several minutes before publishing blocks to Ethereum. If you want to get transactions quickly, you can run in \"L2 sync mode\" which will get transactions directly from the Sequencer.\r\n\r\nWhen Bedrock goes live, you will be able to get \"unsafe\" blocks from the L2 p2p network which will become \"safe\" blocks when confirmed/published to Ethereum.\r\n",
